e Persian king Ahasuerus. Her Hebrew name was <i>Hadassah</i> ‘myrtle’, and the form <i>Esther</i> is said to be a Persian translation of this, although others derive it from Persian <i>stara</i> ‘star’. It may also be a Hebrew form of the name of the Persian goddess <i>Ishtar</i>. According to the book of the Bible that bears her name, Esther managed, by her perception and persuasion, to save large numbers of the Jews from the evil machinations of the royal counsellor Haman.  See also  Hester ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Esther IJsendaal was born in 1424. She married Jan Pietersz van Afferden in 1454, in Holland, Netherlands. They were the parents of at least 2 sons."},"et":{"       1424–":"1424–Surnud","1420–1483":"1420–1483","1455–1516":"1455–1516","1457–Male":"1457–Surnud","1424–Female":"1424–Surnud","       1424":"1424","       1457":"1457","1424":"1424","1457":"1457","1455":"1455","       1454":"1454","1420":"1420","1483":"1483","1516":"1516","Of Middelkoop,South Holland,Neth":"Holland, Madalmaad","Middelkoop, Zuid-Holland, Nederland":"Middelkoop, Zuid-Holland, Madalmaad"},"fi":{"       1424–":"1424–Kuollut","1420–1483":"1420–1483","1455–1516":"1455–1516","1457–Male":"1457–Kuollut","1424–Female":"1424–Kuollut","       1424":"1424","       1457":"1457","1424":"1424","1457":"1457","1455":"1455","       1454":"1454","1420":"1420","1483":"1483","1516":"1516","Of Middelkoop,South Holland,Neth":"Holland, Alankomaat","Middelkoop, Zuid-Holland, Nederland":"Middelkoop, Zuid-Holland, Alankomaat"},"fr":{"       1424–":"1424–Décédée","1420–1483":"1420–1483","1455–1516":"1455–1516","1457–Male":"1457–Décédé","1424–Female":"1424–Décédée","       1424":"1424","       1457":"1457","1424":"1424","1457":"1457","1455":"1455","       1454":"1454","1420":"1420","1483":"1483","1516":"1516","Of Middelkoop,South Holland,Neth":"Holland, Pays-Bas","Middelkoop, Zuid-Holland, Nederland":"Middelkoop, Hollande-Méridionale, Pays-Bas","lifeSummary":"Esther IJsendaal est née en 1424. Ell